
DDACE - Distributed Design and Analysis of Computer Experiments

DDACE is a package of algorithms for rapid design space exploration
through computer experiments and their analyis.  The software package
is predominantly written in C++, with a few components written in C or
Fortran.

DDACE is distributed under the GNU Lesser General Public License.  It
is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify it under the
terms of the GNU Lesser General Public License as published by the
Free Software Foundation; either version 2.1 of the License, or (at
your option) any later version.  A copy of this license is included in
the "GNU_LGPL" file, and is also available online from
http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html.  Also refer to the COPYRIGHT
file for important U.S. Government legal notices.

The DDACE distribution contains libraries which are available
separately under compatible licensing terms.  In particular, MARS and
BOSE are available under the StatLib licensing agreement.  A copy of
this license is included in the "LICENSE_MARS" and "LICENSE_BOSE" files
in the src/FATools and src/Bose directories, respectively, and is also
available online from http://lib.stat.cmu.edu/graphmod/submissions.


